AC   P0A4F8; P35121;
Octopine-binding periplasmic protein precursor.
"Characterization of a putative periplasmic transport system for
octopine accumulation encoded by Agrobacterium tumefaciens Ti plasmid
pTiA6.";
"Opine transport genes in the octopine (occ) and nopaline (noc)
catabolic regions in Ti plasmids of Agrobacterium tumefaciens.";
-!- FUNCTION: Component of the octopine active transport system
    probably consisting of four subunits: Q, M, P and T.
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Periplasm.
-!- INDUCTION: By octopine.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the bacterial solute-binding protein 3
    family.
Periplasmic; Plasmid; Signal; Transport.
